## Day 9: File Compression & Archiving

## 📁 1. Understanding Archive Formats

Common archive formats:
- `.tar` – Archive (no compression)
- `.gz`, `.gzip` – Compressed file
- `.tar.gz`, `.tgz` – Compressed archive
- `.zip` – Compressed archive (cross-platform)

---

## 📦 2. Creating and Extracting Archives

### 🗃️ Create `.tar` Archive

tar -cvf archive.tar file1 file2 folder/


📂 Extract .tar Archive
tar -xvf archive.tar

📦 Create .tar.gz Archive (with compression)
tar -czvf archive.tar.gz folder/

📂 Extract .tar.gz Archive
tar -xzvf archive.tar.gz

🗜️ 3. Compressing Files and Directories

📌 Using gzip (compress single file)
gzip file.txt
gunzip file.txt.gz
📌 Using zip (for multiple files)
zip archive.zip file1 file2 folder/
unzip archive.zip
